general advantages as from a, c, d, f–j;
l. high sensitivity.

A recent example uses an indicator dye (Py-1) comprising pyrylium groups [11] that responds only to primary but not to secondary and tertiary amines on dipsticks. The BA nucleophile converts the pyrylium moiety of Py-1 into the respective pyridinium salt which can visually be seen by a color change from blue (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
